#instructions
install.R      write line that says    install.packages("readr")    do this through github and push to main

Follow resource 1 steps through step 5
After adding other specified files like runtime escript etc all through github and pushing to main open binder and go to R and put in the following to test the environment
library(readr)
packageVersion("readr")
read_csv(system.file("extdata/mtcars.csv", package = "readr"))

next run this code    it is from source 2 and works better than the way described in source 1   loads additional packages
remotes::install_github("karthik/holepunch")

Resume to step 6 from source 1  add badge to readme.md and push through github directly to main after this people can click on the icon in your repo and be directly taken to your binder

